request.description:
A **pre-authorization** is a temporary hold of a specific amount of the available balance on a credit or debit card. The pre-authorization is not a charge, hence no funds are debited from an account.  Fund will be debited upon **completion** (refer to the completion request below).

Pre-Auths can either be **aggregate** or **incremental**.

+ **Aggregate**: the amount debited to the account is the amount of the completion, irrespective of the previously sent pre-auths.
  + Pre-Auth of $10
  + Pre-Auth of $15
  + Completion of $5 (amount debited is $5)
+ **Incremental**: the amount debited to the account is the sum of amounts taken from all pre-auths.
  + Pre-Auth of $10
  + Pre-Auth of $15
  + Completion (amount debited is $25)

When creating a number of related pre-auths, each sub-sequent pre-auth must be linked with the original pre-auth.  This can be achieved by providing the original pre-auth resource ID and passing it through the originalAuth relationship.  For example:

First aggregate pre-auth request body example
```	
	{
	  "data": {
	    "type": "authorisations",
	    "attributes": {
	        "cardNumber" : "4001232312234051",
	        ...
	    },
	    "relationships": {
	      "merchant": {
	        "data": {
	          "type": "merchants",
	          "id": "clientNumber=41123321"
	        }
	      }
	    }
	  }
	}
```

Second aggregate pre-auth request body example linked to first pre-auth via the originalAuth relationship.
```
	{
	  "data": {
	    "type": "authorisations",
	    "attributes": {
	        "cardNumber" : "4001232312234051",
	        ...
	    },
	    "relationships": {
	      "merchant": {
	        "data": {
	          "type": "merchants",
	          "id": "clientNumber=41123321"
	        }
	      },
	      "originalAuth": {
	        "data": {
	          "type": "authorisations",
	          "id": "transactionID=5d655522-f1ad329e92-fe94c3&transmissionDate=2019-08-27T20:34:50"
	        }
	      }
	    }
	  }
	}
```

